<p>SassMeister is a playground for <a href="http://sass-lang.com">Sass</a>. Add some Sass and SassMeister will show you the rendered CSS. SassMeister supports both <a href="http://thesassway.com/articles/sass-vs-scss-which-syntax-is-better">Sass and SCSS syntaxes</a>, all <a href="http://sass-lang.com/docs/yardoc/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html#output_style">output styles</a>, and a growing number of <a href="http://compass-style.org/">Compass</a> extensions and Sass libraries. Current extensions are: 
<% 
  links = Array.new()
  @plugins.each do |plugin, info|
    links.push("<a href=\"#{info[:url]}\">#{plugin}<a>")
  end 
%><%=links.to_sentence%></p>

<p>SassMeister is a project of <a href="http://jedfoster.com/">Jed Foster</a> and <a href="http://www.dalesande.com">Dale Sande</a>, who hope that the Sass community will find it useful. A <a href="http://www.meetup.com/SASSlang/">Seattle Sass Meetup</a> presentation by <a href="https://peepcode.com">PeepCode Screencasts</a> inspired the name.</p>
